## Chrome extension

### manifest.json
```json
{
  "manifest_version": 3,
  "permissions": ["storage", "tabs", "scripting", "declarativeNetRequest"],
  "host_permissions": [""],
  "background": { "service_worker": "background.js" },
  "action": { "default_popup": "popup.html" }
}
```

### background.js (service worker)
Responsibilities — only these:
1. Poll Supabase REST API every 15 seconds for active flight (`GET /rest/v1/flights?status=eq.active`)
2. On active flight found: extract `blocked_sites`, call `updateBlockingRules(domains)`
3. On no active flight: clear all blocking rules
4. On distraction blocked: `POST /rest/v1/sessions_log` to increment `distractions_blocked_count`

Use `chrome.declarativeNetRequest.updateDynamicRules()` for all blocking.
Blocked domains redirect to `blocked.html` (bundled in extension).

Auth: store Supabase session token in `chrome.storage.local` after user logs in via web app. Web app writes to `chrome.storage` on login — extension reads it on startup.

### popup.html
Minimal: show elapsed time if flight active, show "No active flight" otherwise.
One button: "Start quick flight" → opens web app `/preflight` in new tab.
No session logic in the popup.

