## Sync contract between web app and extension

The web app owns session start/stop. The extension is a passive consumer.

| Event | Web App action | Extension reaction |
|---|---|---|
| User starts flight | INSERT flights (status=active) | Next poll picks it up, activates blocking |
| User ends flight | UPDATE flights (status=completed) | Next poll clears rules |
| Tab blocked | — | POST increment to sessions_log |
| Extension opens | Reads chrome.storage for token | Polls immediately |

Polling interval: 15s. Acceptable latency. Do not implement websockets in the extension.

