## Design system

Reference: `/stitch_flight_mode_focus_app/` in the root directory.

This directory contains:
- `stitch_design.md` — complete design system (colors, typography, spacing, component rules)
- Individual screen HTML files — one per page, pixel-accurate

Your job is to **replicate these screens in React**, not reinterpret them.
Strip the HTML into components. Extract inline styles into Tailwind classes or CSS variables.
Do not invent new UI. Do not substitute components. If it's in the HTML, build it. If it's not, don't add it.

### Mapping: HTML file → React page

| HTML file | React route | Component |
|---|---|---|
| `preflight.html` | `/preflight` | `pages/PreFlight.tsx` |
| `active_flight.html` | `/flight/:id` | `pages/ActiveFlight.tsx` |
| `post_flight.html` | `/debrief/:id` | `pages/Debrief.tsx` |
| `analytics.html` | `/analytics` | `pages/Analytics.tsx` |
| `logbook.html` | `/logbook` | `pages/Logbook.tsx` |
| `blocked.html` | (extension only) | `apps/extension/blocked.html` — copy as-is, no React needed |
| `popup.html` | (extension only) | `apps/extension/popup.html` — copy as-is, no React needed |

### Process per screen
1. Read the HTML file
2. Identify repeating structures → extract as components into `src/components/`
3. Wire real data where the HTML has placeholder text (timer, route, stats)
4. Preserve all classnames, spacing, and color values exactly

Dark theme. Background base: `#070B14`. Surface: `#0D1825`. Elevated: `#131E2E`.

Accents:
- Active/success: `#1DB88A` (radar green)
- Interactive/info: `#4FC3F7` (altitude blue)  
- Warning: `#F0A500` (caution amber)

Text: primary `#E8F4FF`, secondary `#7EB8CC`, muted `#4A7C9A`.

Rules:
- No borders as dividers — use background color shifts
- No heavy drop shadows — use tonal layering
- Corner radius: 8px standard, 4px for small tags
- Font: monospace for timer and telemetry data, sans-serif for UI text
- All tags/status badges use monospace, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.08em

